# Pattern: time-based SLA / operational metric.
# Illustrates: duration calculation, tighter freshness window, strict null rates on timing columns.
Metric: First Response Time (P50)
Description: Median time in minutes from when a support ticket is opened to the first agent response.
Owner: customer-support
Tags: operations, sla, customer-experience

Source: support_tickets, agent_messages

Given all tickets opened in the last 30 days
  And the ticket has at least one agent response
  And the ticket channel is "email" or "chat"
  And the ticket priority is not "spam"

When we calculate
  Then compute first_response_time as agent_response_at minus ticket_opened_at
  And take the 50th percentile across all tickets
  And express the result in minutes

The result is "First Response Time (P50)"

Trust:
  Freshness must be less than 2 hours
  Null rate on ticket_opened_at must be 0%
  Null rate on agent_response_at must be less than 5%
  Row count must not drop more than 20% day over day
  Value must be between 1 and 240
  Value must not change more than 25% week over week
